1
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:40,660
Auntie, look!

2
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,820
This is the lake-view apartment I was telling you about.

3
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:42,850
Over there?

4
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,260
- Right? - That's the park.

5
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,410
Isn't that just a pond?

6
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:46,770
No, it's right across the bridge.

7
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,210
Hmm... looks nice.

8
00:01:48,230 --> 00:01:48,930
Alright.

9
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:49,690
As long as you like it,

10
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:50,690
that's all that matters.

11
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:51,410
Yeah, we can...

12
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:51,980
Right?

13
00:01:52,510 --> 00:01:53,100
Hello.

14
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,900
This is my daughter.

15
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,460
Hi.

16
00:01:58,590 --> 00:02:00,180
Auntie always talks about

17
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,460
how kind and caring you are.

18
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,740
Our car's coming soon.

19
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,620
Why don't you come with us?

20
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,180
Right, Auntie?

21
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:04,540
Yeah.

22
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,290
Where to?

23
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:06,380
What are you talking about?

24
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,490
To check out the apartment.

25
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,730
Auntie didn't mention it?

26
00:02:08,870 --> 00:02:09,660
Here, take a look.

27
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,890
This lake-view unit

28
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,260
has a fantastic location,

29
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,570
great sunlight,

30
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:14,850
and a lovely neighborhood,

31
00:02:14,870 --> 00:02:15,690
perfect for retirees!

32
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,610
No, thanks.

33
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:18,100
It's okay, just have a look.

34
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,060
The layout is...

35
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,100
I said no.

36
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,340
She and I have things to talk about.

37
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,010
Alright then.

38
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,410
Auntie, I'll head out.

39
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:25,690
Let's keep in touch, okay?

40
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:26,340
Sure.

41
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:27,170
Bye!

42
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,290
Take care!

43
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:30,130
Okay, Auntie.

44
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,980
Don't just chat with random people like that.

45
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,540
Why are you giving them your number?

46
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,380
These people prey on the elderly, you know that, right?

47
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,100
I know.

48
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:40,570
Come, sit down.

49
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:44,850
Listen,

50
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,690
I just play along

51
00:02:46,710 --> 00:02:49,060
with them for fun.

52
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:50,850
They're so sweet with their words!

53
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:51,850
They even remind me, "Auntie,

54
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,170
it's raining today,

55
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,820
bring an umbrella!"

56
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,220
No matter what you say,

57
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:58,290
how much you say, they never get tired of talking!

58
00:02:58,310 --> 00:02:59,100
And the best part?

59
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,380
They give out

60
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,220
free gifts

61
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,540
just for chatting,

62
00:03:03,710 --> 00:03:04,730
eggs,

63
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:07,170
umbrellas, little fans, toothbrushes...

64
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:08,500
even bath mitts!

65
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,730
Do you want some?

66
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:11,340
Wow, you're sharp.

67
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,340
But aren't you afraid of getting scammed?

68
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,980
Hey, you haven't eaten yet, have you?

69
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,540
Come on,

70
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,540
let's go grab a bite at Zhou Kai's restaurant!

71
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,540
- Come. - No,

72
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:22,170
I'm good.

73
00:03:22,190 --> 00:03:23,260
I just wanted to talk to you for a bit.

74
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,060
Here, have some water.

75
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:33,100
Do you remember back in high school entrance exams?

76
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,340
I got the top score in the whole town!

77
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,820
You? First place?

78
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:40,340
Wow, that's impressive.

79
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,610
Back then, you said it was worth celebrating

80
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,010
and took me out for braised pork trotters.

81
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:51,380
That was my first time ever eating at a restaurant.

82
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:55,850
Pork trotters, huh?

83
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,410
That meal was expensive!

84
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,610
And your brother, Zhou Kai,

85
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,820
he was such a troublemaker!

86
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,540
Remember how he slapped

87
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:07,540
your teacher's son?

88
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,260
She was furious, demanded a huge compensation

89
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:11,610
and penalty,

90
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:13,610
and wanted to expel him.

91
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,570
I was so worried.

92
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:15,690
Then one day, out of nowhere,

93
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,700
she called me in and said,

94
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,100
"Forget it. No punishment,

95
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,730
no compensation."

96
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,730
That was great news, right?

97
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,170
We had to celebrate!

98
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:27,170
What was it we ate again?

99
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:28,220
Braised...

100
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,410
Braised pork trotters.

101
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:34,490
Oh, by the way, about that house,

102
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,170
look over there, past the bridge.

103
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:38,290
That young guy already signed for it.

104
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,410
Over there.

105
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,050
See that little hole over there?

106
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,220
And look, there's a yellow duck!

107
00:04:59,310 --> 00:05:00,850
Surprised?

108
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,850
You're home early.

109
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,250
Have you been waiting long?

110
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,050
Not too bad.

111
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:14,020
There was a little issue with my intel.

112
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:16,810
My source told me you'd be home early this afternoon.

113
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:19,290
I rushed back to get everything ready,

114
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:22,050
after all, this is our first time

115
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,850
celebrating our wedding anniversary alone.

116
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:25,610
Let's open the wine!

117
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,660
I brought some dishes to go with it.

118
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:34,850
I didn't even know you bought this.

119
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:36,140
I actually made steak for you.

120
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,020
Want to try some?

121
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,100
Maybe later.

122
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:41,290
Today, I'm really craving braised pork trotters.

123
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:42,780
Looks good.

124
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,980
What do you call this dish back in your hometown?

125
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,700
Just Minnan-style braised pork trotters.

126
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,700
If you like it,

127
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,220
I can learn how to make it.

128
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,540
Then you can have it anytime.

129
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,810
Otherwise, we're just eating steak over and over again.

130
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,810
No need, you already cook so much.

131
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,100
You don't have to learn this too.

132
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,370
Don't flatter me like that,

133
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,930
or I'll get cocky.

134
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:04,220
After all, when I proposed,

135
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:07,250
I made you a bunch of promises.

136
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:11,140
Like always listening to you,

137
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:13,140
never letting you feel wronged.

138
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:16,700
But honestly, I've barely kept any of them.

139
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,050
Except for handling all the household chores,

140
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,490
on that one, I did okay.

141
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,700
Actually, I know how to cook too.

142
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,220
Really?

143
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:29,250
Yeah, when I was a kid, I cooked at home every day.

144
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:31,370
You've never really talked much

145
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,540
about your childhood.

146
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:35,050
You mentioned your family passed away,

147
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:36,140
so I didn't want to ask,

148
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,540
in case it made you sad.

149
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,460
Tell me about your childhood.

150
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,250
All I remember

151
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:44,100
is that chubby photo of you I once saw.

152
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,540
What were you like as a kid?

153
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,220
As a kid?

154
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:48,900
I was dashing and charming,

155
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,930
adored by thousands of girls.

156
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,580
Is that joke too cliche?

157
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,410
Yeah.

158
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:55,780
Especially with the braised pork trotter.

159
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,610
Maybe it's because my parents

160
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,020
had me pretty late in life.

161
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:05,370
They loved me very much, of course,

162
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,460
but our home always

163
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,490
felt different from my classmates'.

164
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:10,490
Other families were always lively and bustling,

165
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,660
but our house was always quiet.

166
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,140
Did I ever tell you

167
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,540
that I was really short as a kid?

168
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,050
I only hit this height

169
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,730
when I got to high school.

170
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,810
I was always seated

171
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:23,170
in the front row at school.

172
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:24,490
No one really noticed me.

173
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:25,930
I didn't have many friends either.

174
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,140
Every day, I'd go to school alone,

175
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,780
then come home,

176
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,900
go straight to my room to read,

177
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,930
and then back to school again.

178
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:35,220
A simple, repetitive cycle.

179
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,250
I would've never guessed.

180
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,250
Your parents seem so warm and outgoing now,

181
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,140
and you...

182
00:07:41,510 --> 00:07:43,930
I've practically become a social butterfly, right?

183
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,660
Do you know when I started to change?

184
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,700
When I was studying in Germany.

185
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:51,340
Back then,

186
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:56,250
I was alone in a foreign country,

187
00:07:56,630 --> 00:07:57,610
with no family, no friends.

188
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,660
I didn't even speak the language.

189
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,340
To practice my speaking,

190
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,730
I forced myself to talk to people more.

191
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:04,780
Over time,

192
00:08:05,870 --> 00:08:07,220
I ended up opening up.

193
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,140
Back to my childhood,

194
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,340
maybe I was just too lonely back then.

195
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,610
So I always imagined that one day,

196
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,410
when I had a family of my own,

197
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:21,050
it would be full of laughter and warmth.

198
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:22,810
Even if there were occasional arguments,

199
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:24,980
even if the house was sometimes chaotic,

200
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,580
to me,

201
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,730
that's what warmth feels like.

202
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,530
If that's the case,

203
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,130
our home must seem awfully quiet.

204
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,300
You know, one of my most vivid memories

205
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,220
was the first time you spent Chinese New Year at my house.

206
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,220
New Year's Eve,

207
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:46,610
the whole factory compound

208
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:48,060
was filled with fireworks and firecrackers,

209
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,940
popping and crackling nonstop.

210
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,490
The Spring Festival Gala was on TV.

211
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,890
My dad, with his loud voice,

212
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:55,770
was calling up everyone he knew to send New Year's wishes.

213
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,300
My mom was bustling around,

214
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,730
preparing dishes for the relatives coming over the next day.

215
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,370
You were busy too, walking back and forth,

216
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,300
constantly on the phone,

217
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,890
giving instructions about things at the hospital.

218
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:05,820
That night

219
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,130
was the happiest night

220
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:09,340
of my life.

221
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,340
Thinking about it now...

222
00:09:16,510 --> 00:09:19,940
If in that picture,

223
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:23,340
there was also our child...

224
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:27,250
That would be perfect.

225
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,300
Do you remember in Munich,

226
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,370
that Turkish supermarket called Ken's?

227
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:43,420
It was about two kilometers from our hospital.

228
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,130
Of course, I remember.

229
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:46,850
They had a wrap

230
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:48,130
that you loved, right?

231
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:50,250
I didn't love it at all.

232
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,490
It's just that my shift ended at 7 PM,

233
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:53,610
and that was exactly when they had a 50% discount.

234
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,940
So that was my only choice.

235
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,010
I...

236
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,820
Back then, I actually thought you loved eating those wraps.

237
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,850
So I foolishly bought them for you every day.

238
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,100
If I had known...

239
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:12,580
The winter of 2017 was especially cold.

240
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:13,940
Do you remember?

241
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,980
After Oktoberfest, there was a heavy snowfall.

242
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:17,770
Whenever I had a night shift,

243
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,220
you would bring that wrap

244
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,650
and a cup of coffee to wait for me.

245
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,980
One night, I had to perform an extra surgery,

246
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,610
and by the time I came out, it was past 2 AM.

247
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:27,770
I didn't see you there,

248
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,220
and I panicked.

249
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:30,980
I called you,

250
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,460
but your phone was off.

251
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,980
I ran to your department to find you,

252
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,940
and from a distance, I saw you talking to Dr. Chase,

253
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,530
discussing work.

254
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,180
I just sat on a hospital chair, keeping you company,

255
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:45,220
drinking bitter coffee,

256
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,850
eating that impossibly hard wrap,

257
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,340
staying with you until dawn.

258
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,420
Then, we went back to our apartment together.

259
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:52,730
Do you remember?

260
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:56,650
I don't remember at all.

261
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:57,940
It's like I lost that memory.

262
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:01,250
I was so terrible back then.

263
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,730
What kind of work could be so important,

264
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:03,940
- that I had to talk about it at that hour? - You weren't terrible at all.

265
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,460
That night,

266
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,850
I knew that you were the person I wanted to rely on for the rest of my life.

267
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,850
Because we could work hard together,

268
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:11,700
talk about work together, endure hardships together.

269
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:14,460
That night,

270
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:17,340
was when I felt happiest.

271
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:26,340
Haven't we

272
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:28,940
always been like this?

273
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,340
We started Gemu together,

274
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:32,580
we face

275
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,850
work challenges together.

276
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,180
See? We should communicate

277
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,650
more like this, right?

278
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:37,980
A lot of problems,

279
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,730
as long as we talk things through,

280
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,100
can be solved.

281
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:44,370
Right?

282
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:56,650
You just said that your most beautiful vision

283
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,700
is a family together

284
00:11:58,720 --> 00:11:59,770
